QUESTIONS
1. Besides TCP, what other protocols can be used?
ICMP and UDP can be used.

2. When traversing to a website, does the path remain constant every time?
No, network paths can change due to dynamic routing, load balancing, or network congestion.

3. If a packet dies before reaching the target, what type of packet is returned?
An ICMP Type 11 (Time Exceeded) packet.

4. Can the whois command be used to discover the owner of an AS number?
Yes, querying an AS number (e.g., whois AS15169) returns the registration details, including the organization name.